&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Mozilla?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Mozilla Corporation is the non-profit-backed technology company that has shaped the internet for the better over the last 25 years. We make pioneering brands like Firefox, the privacy-minded web browser. Now, with more than 225 million people around the world using our products each month, we’re shaping the next 25 years of technology and helping to reclaim an internet built for people, not companies. Our work focuses on diverse areas including AI, social media, security and more. And we’re doing this while never losing our focus on our core mission – to make the internet better for people.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The Mozilla Corporation is wholly owned by the non-profit 501(c) Mozilla Foundation. This means we aren’t beholden to any shareholders — only to our mission. Along with thousands of volunteer contributors and collaborators all over the world, Mozillians design, build and distribute open-source software that enables people to enjoy the internet on their terms.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this team and role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Mozilla’s mission is to champion the internet as a global public resource, measured through a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blog.mozilla.org/wp-content/blogs.dir/278/files/2025/11/Mozilla-Summary-Portfolio-Strategy.pdf&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;double bottom line&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;: advancing that mission while succeeding in the market. At Mozilla Corporation, this means building and scaling trusted, user-first &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/products/&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;products&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;, like &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.firefox.com/en-US/&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Firefox&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;, that give people meaningful control over their online experience, while supporting a more open, competitive, and sustainable tech ecosystem. The global public policy team enables this by shaping laws and regulatory frameworks that support our open source technologies, strengthen user choice and privacy, and ensure fair competition to create the conditions for responsible innovation and long-term growth.Do you like working on big-picture problems? Join us to influence the future of tech policy!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;In this role, you will engage with government stakeholders, industry partners, and civil society, advocating for public policy positions that align with our mission and support responsible innovation in technology. You will be responsible for raising the profile of Mozilla and Firefox in the UK, ensuring consistent engagement with our stakeholders, and coordinating input from subject matter experts on the global policy team. As such, you will lead end-to-end policy campaign development and execution across key issues such as privacy, competition, and AI in the UK, while contributing to and supporting related efforts at EU level.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You will also collaborate with our internal product and engineering teams to provide expert advice on public policy implications related to the rollout of new products. This role reports to the Head of Public Policy EU.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;This is a high-impact role for someone who understands both the technical landscape and the policymaking process—and who wants to help build a better internet.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Engage with UK policymakers, regulators, and other stakeholders to advocate for policy frameworks that support the open web and Mozilla’s product initiatives. Focus on issues including competition, privacy, AI, and consumer protection while supporting alignment with EU regulatory developments and stakeholders&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Build public policy campaigns from the ground up and drive their execution to raise Mozilla’s profile in the UK and shape ongoing policy discussions that impact our products and the open web, including planning, delivery, and evaluation of end-to-end advocacy strategies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Represent Mozilla in external forums, industry groups, and other public venues on policy issues, and ensure our views are accurately and effectively communicated, including through policy events, thought leadership, and coordinated advocacy with third-party organisations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Monitor, analyze, and communicate internally about emerging policy issues, regulatory developments, and global trends affecting Mozilla&#39;s products and services across the UK and the EU.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Translate complex technical concepts into clear, concise, and actionable policy insights and recommendations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Lead and manage policy-related projects end-to-end, including coordination of timelines, stakeholders, deliverables, and external partners.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree or equivalent practical experience with at least 5 years of experience working on technology policy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Demonstrated experience working in the UK policy environment (e.g. UK Government, Westminister, CMA, ICO etc), with familiarity and exposure to EU policy processes and stakeholders.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Ability to manage multiple priorities with high attention to detail, manage external policy agencies and drive projects to successful completion, including structured delivery of policy campaigns, events, and advocacy initiatives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Excellent cross-functional skills with experience working with international teams and a variety of collaborators.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strong policy writing, research, and analysis skills attuned to communicating key information to decision makers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience in competition and privacy policy, and/or exposure to civil society, or non-profit technology environments, is strongly preferred.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll get:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Generous performance-based bonus plans to all eligible employees - we share in our success as one team&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Rich medical, dental, and vision coverage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Generous retirement contributions with 100% immediate vesting (regardless of whether you contribute)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Quarterly all-company wellness days where everyone takes a pause together&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Country specific holidays plus a day off for your birthday&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;One-time home office stipend&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Annual professional development budget&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Quarterly well-being stipend&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Considerable paid parental leave&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Employee referral bonus program&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Other benefits (life/AD&amp;amp;D, disability, EAP, etc. - varies by country)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Mozilla&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mozilla exists to build the Internet as a public resource accessible to all because we believe that open and free is better than closed and controlled. When you work at Mozilla, you give yourself a chance to make a difference in the lives of Web users everywhere. And you give us a chance to make a difference in your life every single day. Join us to work on the Web as the platform and help create more opportunity and innovation for everyone online.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commitment to diversity, equity, inclusion, and belonging&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mozilla understands that valuing diverse creative practices and forms of knowledge are crucial to and enrich the company’s core mission.&amp;nbsp; We encourage applications from everyone, including members of all equity-seeking communities, such as (but certainly not limited to) women, racialized and Indigenous persons, persons with disabilities, persons of all sexual orientation&lt;span style=&quot;color: #003366;&quot;&gt;s, &lt;/span&gt;gender identities, and expressions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will ensure that qualified individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodations to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment, as appropriate. Please contact us at &lt;a class=&quot;external-link&quot; href=&quot;mailto:hiringaccommodation@mozilla.com&quot;&gt;hiringaccommodation@mozilla.com&lt;/a&gt; to request accommodation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate on the basis of race (including hairstyle and texture), religion (including religious grooming and dress practices), gender, gender identity, gender expression, color, national origin, pregnancy, ancestry, domestic partner status, disability, sexual orientation, age, genetic predisposition, medical condition, marital status, citizenship status, military or veteran status, or any other basis covered by applicable laws.&amp;nbsp; Mozilla will not tolerate discrimination or harassment based on any of these characteristics or any other unlawful behavior, conduct, or purpose.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Group: C&lt;/p&gt;
